ie6 does not support:

multiple class declarations attached to an element, e.g.
	li.expandable.open
	... can only do one => li.expandable

psuedo hover applied to li:
	li:hover



also note:

firefox 3.0 does not support pseudo li:first-child / li:last-child declarations (FF 3.5+ does)



you can try attaching HTC files to elements to give the behavior but it is problematic

... see \htc floder

body { behavior: url(myhack.htc); }





IE conditionals..


<!--[if IE]> .. <![endif]-->

<!--[if IE 6]> .. <![endif]-->

<!--[if IE 7]> .. <![endif]-->
